This paper is about cross-lingual word embeddings, which are commonly used in natural language processing (NLP) tasks such as machine translation and cross-lingual information retrieval. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which focuses on NLP and related topics. The paper also discusses the use of unsupervised and semi-supervised learning methods, which are common in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG and cs.AI). The evaluation of the models involves analyzing their performance on different training corpora and target languages, which could fall under information retrieval (cs.IR) or computer vision (cs.CV) categories.
